Making this responsive, I made sure <strong>the experience remained in tack while only stripping away elements that were not of necessity</strong>. Things like the <strong>breadcrumbs were simplified</strong> to provide only a way back instead of the entire chain leading to that point to fit better within the restricted space. <strong>Carousels were morphed to create a peeking effect from the edge of the browser window</strong> to encourage scroll interaction. And finally, navigational items were repositioned to be <strong>more accessible by a user's thumb</strong>.";}i:371;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:16:"_section_1_blurb";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd211f1626a";}i:372;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:20:"appendices_2_details";s:10:"meta_value";s:68:"<dl>
