For Galveston Chamber to be able to invest in the business community, it needs the community to invest in them. But this wasn't easy for the community to do. The registration process wasn't electronic and required mail-ins to complete. They may be the oldest chamber in Texas, but there was no reason their process for joining had to be anymore.

The fundamental method of attracting a user's attention, <strong>call-to-actions, was the first step I took</strong> towards getting Galveston on the right track. These were included within the main navigation as well as embedded within content as its own section, but <strong>no further down then 60% of the page's total length</strong> for the best probability of being noticed. All <strong>call-to-actions are forwarded to a registration page</strong> hosted by Chamber Master, a CMS specifically developed for a chamber of commerce, for any business to sign up at any time. For those seeking information before committing, a copious library of events, tiers, benefits, programs, and more is accessible to all users.";}i:389;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:16:"_section_4_blurb";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd211f1626a";}i:390;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:39:"section_5_images_w_caption_show_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:1:"0";}i:391;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:40:"_section_5_images_w_caption_show_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5f1235c8ed299";}i:392;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:34:"section_5_images_w_caption_gallery";s:10:"meta_value";s:61:"a:4:{i:0;s:3:"215";i:1;s:3:"217";i:2;s:2:"52";i:3;s:3:"341";}";}i:393;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:35:"_section_5_images_w_caption_gallery";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd33e259ccf";}i:394;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:26:"section_5_images_w_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:395;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:27:"_section_5_images_w_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd33d559cce";}i:396;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:15:"section_6_blurb";s:10:"meta_value";s:1185:"<h2>Converging Platforms</h2>
Galveston Chamber utilized Chamber Master to regulate their content. Years of practice made them comfortable with its system, and they were seeking to preserve that. Though this was a problem for the development team to solve, I still worked closely throughout the process to learn of the limitations that may affect the design.

The developers' research found that there was ultimately no concerns to be had with the design. However, other challenges appeared in its placeâthe first being able to call individual elements from Chamber Master's API. Initial tests showed everything inside one string, which proved cumbersome for what we needed. The developers eventually devised a way to separate the elements into an array for us to cherry-pick from. Unfortunately, this led to our next problemâa set limit of 50 calls allowed to the API per day. This limitation, if left unwatched, could quickly be exhausted by one site visit. The team and I had to construct a schedule in which updates would automatically be applied to the website. A majority of these updates took place during business hours, while only a few happened outside that timeframe.";}i:397;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:16:"_section_6_blurb";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd211f1626a";}i:398;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:39:"section_7_images_w_caption_show_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:1:"0";}i:399;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:40:"_section_7_images_w_caption_show_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5f1235c8ed299";}i:400;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:34:"section_7_images_w_caption_gallery";s:10:"meta_value";s:20:"a:1:{i:0;s:3:"217";}";}i:401;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:35:"_section_7_images_w_caption_gallery";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd33e259ccf";}i:402;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:26:"section_7_images_w_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:0:"";}i:403;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:27:"_section_7_images_w_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:19:"field_5efd33d559cce";}i:404;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s:3:"224";s:8:"meta_key";s:39:"section_8_images_w_caption_show_caption";s:10:"meta_value";s:1:"0";}i:405;O:8:"stdClass":3:{s:7:"post_id";s: